The paper deals with a distributed proof mechanism for certifying the correctness of a solution to a graph problem, specifically the minimum spanning tree problem. This falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) as well as graph theory (cs.DS, cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DM). Additionally, the use of labels and local checking suggests a potential connection to network protocols and security (cs.NI).
